messages.message:
Locally I keep getting disconnected from rabbitmq, anyone else experience this issue?
```[2020-07-08 13:55:11,092: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-3] Read empty data, calling disconnect
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,092: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-3] Disconnected from RabbitMQ at 127.0.0.1:5672 (-1): EOF
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,093: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-3] Connection close detected; result=BlockingConnection__OnClosedArgs(connection=<SelectConnection CLOSED socket=None params=<ConnectionParameters host=127.0.0.1 port=5672 virtual_host=/ ssl=False>>, reason_code=-1, reason_text='EOF')
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,093: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-3] --- Attempting connection with RabbitMQ ---
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,095: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-3] Pika version 0.13.0 connecting to 127.0.0.1:5672
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,103: INFO/ForkPoolWorker-3] Created channel=1
[2020-07-08 13:55:11,110: ERROR/ForkPoolWorker-3] Could not export entity [0e09d752-0445-4155-bdd7-72db0783287d] to endpoint```
@Aaron Vontell that is from the Exporter
Even then `Disconnected from RabbitMQ at 127.0.0.1:5672 (-1): EOF`?
We need to investigate and look at how we can keep the rabbit-mq session alive
the next time we go to export, the exporter establishes a new connection
